All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ActionDesire
The Class ActionDesire models the desire to obtain a role which enables certain actions.
ActionInfo
The Record ActionInfo provides a data structure to store an Action combined with additional information about the reasoning process.
Agent
An abstract Java agent.
AgentCooperations
The class AgentCooperations contains all the important methods for a agents cooperation.
AgentCooperations.Cooperation
Record with all the important data of a cooperation.
AgentDebugData
The Record AgentDebugData provides a data structure to store information about an agent.
AgentLogger
Class that extends the functionality of the java.util.logging module to enable that specific log-files can be generated depending on a given string (e. g. one for each agent and/or desire).
AgentMeeting
The class AgentMeeting defines the structure of an AgentMeeting.
AgentMeetings
The class AgentMeetings contains all the important methods for a AgentMeeting.
AgentMeetings.Meeting
The meeting record of all agent meetings.
AgentPanel
The Class AgentPanel defines a Panel to view debug information of an agent including its desires.
AgentPanel.HeaderLabel
The inner Class HeaderLabel defines a header text for labeling different sections of a panel
AgentReport
The Record AgentReport provides a data structure to store important information about the agent.
AgentSurveyStepEvent
The Record AgentSurveyStepEvent stores information about a surveyed agent received by the simulation server.
ArrangeBlockDesire
The class ArrangeBlockDesire models the desire to arrange a block.
AttachAbandonedBlockDesire
The Class AttachAbandonedBlockDesire models the desire to attach an unattached block in vision.
BdiAgent<T>
The abstract Class BdiAgent defines a base class for implementations of the Bdi concept.
BdiAgentV1
The class BdiAgentV1 defines an agent implementation of group 3 in the massim agent contest 2022.
BdiAgentV2
The class BdiAgentV2 defines an agent implementation of group 3 in the massim agent contest 2022.
Belief
The Class Belief defines a data structure to store the agents information about the simulation.
BeliefDesire
The abstract Class BeliefDesire defines a basic framework for implementing a desire which gets it's information from an agents belief.
BooleanInfo
The Record BooleanInfo provides a data structure to store a boolean with a String.
CalcResult
The Record CalcResult stores the path finding result message to an agent with the agent name.
CellType
The Enumeration CellType indicates the type of a certain cell in the GameMap
CellUtils
The Class CellUtils contains helper methods to draw cells of the massim simulation.
ConnectBlockToAgentDesire
The Class ConnectBlockToAgentDesire models the desire to connect a block to another agent.
ConnectMultiBlocksDesire
The class ConnectMultiBlocksDesire models the desire to connect blocks for a multi-block-task.
Convert
The Class Convert contains static methods to convert between massim definitions and definitions defined by the GameMap and its parts.
DebugStepListener
The Interface DebugStepListener defines methods for interaction between the GraphicalDebugger and a class which forwards information to the simulation server.
DeliverAndConnectBlockDesire
The Class DeliverAndConnectBlockDesire models the desire to deliver and connect a block to another agent.
DeliverBlockDesire
The Class DeliverBlockDesire models the desire to deliver a block to another agent.
DesireDebugData
The Record DesireDebugData provides a data structure to store information about a desire of an agent.
DesireUtilities
The class DesireUtilities contains all the methods that are necessary for working the desires .
DigFreeDesire
The Class DigFreeDesire models the desire to free the agent from a deadlock where the agent unintentionally hasn't moved a while.
DirectionUtil
The Class DirectionUtil contains static methods to convert Between string directions, int code directions and Point directions.
DisconnectAllDesire
The Class DisconnectAllDesire models the desire disconnect from all attached blocks and entities.
DisconnectMultiBlocksDesire
The class DisconnectMultiBlocksDesire models the desire to disconnect blocks form a agent after a successfully submitted multi-block-task.
Disposable
The Interface Disposable defines a method to clean resources allocated by a class.
DropBlockDesire
The Class DropBlockDesire models the desire to drop all blocks the agent is currently carrying.
EisSender
The Interface EisSender provides a method to send an action to the simulation server.
EscapeClearDesire
The Class EscapeClearDesire models the desire to avoid regions which have a clear marker attached.
EventName
The Enumeration EventName indicates the event received from a message in BdiAgentV1
ExploreDesire
The Class ExploreDesire models the desire to explore the agents environment.
ExploreMapSizeDesire
The class ExploreMapSizeDesire models the desire to explore the map size.
ExploreMapSizeDesire
The Class ExploreMapSizeDesire models the desire to get information about the map size.
FreedomDesire
The Class FreedomDesire models the desire to stay unconnected to other agents.
GameMap
The Class GameMap stores a two dimensional array of MapCells which map the state of the discovered game map to an internal data structure which is the base for path finding.
GetBlockDesire
The Class GetBlockDesire models the desire to get a block of a certain type and to bring it to the goal zone.
GetBlocksInOrderDesire
The Class GetBlocksInOrderDesire models the desire to rotate attached blocks to fit the requirements of a certain task.
GoAbandonedBlockDesire
The class GoAbandonedBlockDesire models the desire to pick up abandoned blocks.
GoAdoptRoleDesire
The class GoAdoptRoleDesire models the desire to adopt a role.
GoDispenserDesire
The class GoDispenserDesire models the desire to go to a dispenser.
GoGoalZoneDesire
The class GoGoalZoneDesire models the desire to go to (into) a goal zone.
GoNearGoalZoneDesire
The Class GoNearGoalZoneDesire models the desire to be positioned near a goal zone.
GoToGoalZoneDesire
The Class GoToGoalZoneDesire models the desire to be positioned inside of a goal zone.
GoToRoleZoneDesire
The Class GoToRoleZoneDesire models the desire to be positioned inside of a role zone.
GraphicalDebugger
The Class GraphicalDebugger defines a Frame to view debug information of the current simulation and especially of Agents, their path finding and decision making.
GroupDebugData
The Record GroupDebugData defines a data structure to store information about an agent group.
GroupDesireTypes
The Class GroupDesireTypes provides constants which define group desire types.
GuardDispenserDesire
The Class GuardDispenserDesire was designed to test a strategy where a dispenser is blocked by an agent so that the enemy agents cannot get blocks from it anymore.
GuardGoalZoneDesire
The Class GuardGoalZoneDesire models the desire to get the best clearing role and then wait in a goal zone for enemies with blocks, then use clear action on them until they are deactivated and then use clear action on the blocks they were carrying.
Header
The Class Header defines a Panel which displays general information about the simulation, controls for manual interaction with the simulation and the selection of the displayed agent group.
Helper2MultiBlocksDesire
The class Helper2MultiBlocksDesire models the desire of a agent who is the second helper ( has the third block) of a multi-block-task.
HelperMultiBlocksDesire
The class HelperMultiBlocksDesire models the desire of a agent who is the first helper ( has the second block) of a multi-block-task.
IDesire
The Interface IDesire provides methods for interacting with agent desires.
IGraphicalDebugger
The Interface IGraphicalDebugger defines methods for communication between the debugger and the Navi.
IIntention
The Interface IIntention provides methods for accessing the current intention of an agent.
INavi
The Interface INavi defines methods for basic interaction between agents and the Navi.
INaviAgentV1
The Interface INaviAgentV1 defines methods for special interaction between BdiAgentV1 and the Navi.
INaviAgentV2
The Interface INaviAgentV2 defines methods for special interaction between BdiAgentV2 and the Navi.
INaviTest
The Interface INaviTest defines methods for testing the Navi.
InterestingPoint
The Record InterestingPoint defines a data structure to store information about special cells in the GameMap which are used in the path finding process.
ISupervisor
The Interface ISupervisor defines methods to communicate between an Agent and its supervisor.
LocalExploreDesire
The class LocalExploreDesire models the desire to do a local explore.
LooseWeightDesire
The Class LooseWeightDesire models the desire to only have blocks attached which can be used f√ºr active tasks.
MailService
A simple register for agents that forwards messages.
Main
Starts a new scheduler.
MapCell
The Class MapCell stores information of a Cell in the GameMap.
MapCellReport
The Class MapCellReport stores information of the current state of a Cell in the vision of an agent.
MapPanel
The Class MapPanel defines a Panel which displays the simulation map.
MasterMultiBlocksDesire
The class MasterMultiBlocksDesire models the desire for a agent to become a master.
MeetAgentAtGoalZoneDesire
The Class MeetAgentAtGoalZoneDesire models the desire to meet a team mate at a goal zone.
MeetAgentToDeliverBlockDesire
The Class MeetAgentToDeliverBlockDesire models the desire to meet a team mate to transfer an attached block.
MeetAgentToReceiveBlockDesire
The Class MeetAgentToReceiveBlockDesire models the desire to meet a team mate to get a block transferred.
Navi
The Singleton Class Navi acts as an entry point for getting information from the game map.
NormsPanel
The Class NormsPanel defines a Panel which displays the current norms of the simulation.
OrDesire
The Class OrDesire models a combined desire of two sub desires.
PathFinder
The Class PathFinder handles the communication with the OpenGL library GLFW to create and manage OpenGL Contexts.
PathFindingResult
Record with the Pathfindig result.
PathFindingResult
The Record PathFindingResult stores the the distance and direction of a point to another point.
PerceptUtil
The Class PerceptUtil contains static methods to serialize and deserialize Percepts.
Point
The class BdiAgentV2 contains some important methods for point processing in BdiAgentV2.
ProcessEasyTaskDesire
The Class ProcessEasyTaskDesire models the desire to fulfill a single block task.
ProcessOnlySubmittableTaskDesire
The Class ProcessOnlySubmittableTaskDesire models the desire to only work on tasks which deadline hasn't passed already.
ReachableDispenser
The Record ReachableDispenser stores path finding information from an agent to a cell adjacent to a dispenser.
ReachableGoalZone
The Record ReachableGoalZone stores path finding information from an agent to a cell in a goal zone.
ReachableRoleZone
The Record ReachableRoleZone stores path finding information from an agent to a cell in a role zone.
ReachableTeammate
The Record ReachableTeammate stores path finding information from an agent to another agent.
ReceiveAndConnectBlockDesire
The Class ReceiveAndConnectBlockDesire models the desire to receive and connect a block from a team mate to prepare for a two block task.
ReceiveBlockDesire
The Class ReceiveBlockDesire models the desire to receive a block from a team mate and use the block to submit a single block task.
ReportList
The Class ReportList stores a List of MapCellReports and provides methods for managing the reports.

The Class RequestBlockFromDispenserDesire models the desire to request a block from a dispenser.

A scheduler for agent creation and execution.

Status
The enum Status is a important part of the communication of BdiAgentV2.
StepEvent
The Interface StepEvent provides a base type for all Sever Step events.
StepUtilities
The class StepUtilities contains all the methods that are necessary for the correct sequence of a single step .
SubmitDesire
The class SubmitDesire models the desire to submit a task ( block structure).
Supervisable
The Interface Supervisable defines methods for communication between an agent and its supervisor and should be implemented by any agent which has a supervisor.
SupervisableAdapter
The Class SupervisableAdapter creates an Adapter for the Interface Supervisable.
Supervisor
The Class Supervisor defines logic to coordinate a group of agents.
SupervisorEventName
The Enumeration SupervisorEventName indicates the event received from a message in Supervisor
TaskPanel
The Class TaskPanel defines a Panel which displays information about the current tasks of the simulation.
WaitAtGoalZoneDesire
The Class WaitAtGoalZoneDesire models the desire to wait at a goal zone for another agent to construct a two block task.
WaitNearGoalZoneDesire
The Class WaitNearGoalZoneDesire models the desire to wait near a goal zone.
WalkByGetRoleDesire
The Class WalkByGetRoleDesire models the desire to get a role which enables certain actions if the agent has a role zone in vision.
ZoneType
The Enumeration ZoneType indicates the zone type of a certain cell in the GameMap
